WEBVTT

00:02.669 --> 00:04.003
<i>- ♪ Crashing through</i>
<i>the crowded halls ♪</i>

00:04.070 --> 00:05.739
<i>♪ Dodging girls</i>
<i>like Ping-Pong balls ♪</i>

00:05.805 --> 00:07.273
<i>♪ Just to reach the bathroom</i>
<i>on time ♪</i>

00:07.340 --> 00:08.675
<i>♪ Leaping over laundry piles ♪</i>

00:08.742 --> 00:10.577
<i>♪ Diapers you can smell</i>
<i>for miles ♪</i>

00:10.643 --> 00:14.013
<i>♪ Guy's got to do</i>
<i>what he can to survive ♪</i>

00:14.080 --> 00:15.081
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:15.148 --> 00:16.516
<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:16.583 --> 00:17.684
<i>- ♪ Duck, dodge, push,</i>
<i>and shove ♪</i>

00:17.751 --> 00:19.419
<i>♪ Is how we show our love ♪</i>

00:19.486 --> 00:21.454
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house,</i>
<i>in the Loud house ♪</i>

00:21.521 --> 00:22.956
<i>- ♪ One boy and ten girls ♪</i>

00:23.022 --> 00:24.958
<i>♪ Wouldn't trade it</i>
<i>for the world ♪</i>

00:25.024 --> 00:28.094
<i>- ♪ Loud Loud Loud ♪</i>

00:28.161 --> 00:29.429
{\an8}<i>♪ Loud house ♪</i>

00:29.496 --> 00:30.630
{\an8}- Poo-poo.

00:34.734 --> 00:37.670
<i>[exciting music]</i>

00:37.737 --> 00:43.276
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:44.444 --> 00:46.212
[tires screech]

00:46.279 --> 00:47.981
{\an1}- I am so glad
we signed up

00:48.047 --> 00:50.049
{\an1}for those ballroom
dance classes.

00:50.116 --> 00:51.184
{\an3}- Me too.

00:51.251 --> 00:53.820
One tango lesson
and I am a pro.

00:53.887 --> 00:56.523
Ba-rat-ta-ta-ta-ra-yah!

00:56.589 --> 00:57.657
[thud]

00:57.724 --> 00:59.392
- Ow, ow, thorns!

00:59.459 --> 01:02.395
- Doh! Oh, sorry, sorry!
I'll get the first aid kit.

01:02.462 --> 01:03.696
[keys jingle]

01:03.763 --> 01:05.799
[groans]
Those darn kids!

01:05.865 --> 01:06.933
[door bangs]

01:07.000 --> 01:08.268
{\an3}I have told you guys
a million times,

01:08.334 --> 01:09.936
{\an3}you got to lock
the doors at night!

01:10.003 --> 01:12.238
- Come on, Pops.
What's the big whoop?

01:12.305 --> 01:13.807
- Oh, I'll tell you
what the big whoop is.

01:13.873 --> 01:15.508
There've been some burglaries
in the neighborhood,

01:15.575 --> 01:17.110
and I don't want us
to be next.

01:17.177 --> 01:19.979
{\an3}So please, just...lock...
the...dang...door.

01:20.046 --> 01:23.116
It's not that hard!

01:23.183 --> 01:25.018
- Uh...honey?

01:25.084 --> 01:26.853
- Listen, guys,
Dad's right.

01:26.920 --> 01:28.555
We need to start
acting responsible,

01:28.621 --> 01:30.423
or we're gonna lose
all our stuff.

01:30.490 --> 01:32.158
- I don't want to lose my ax!

01:32.225 --> 01:36.095
<i>[sneaky music]</i>

01:36.162 --> 01:38.031
- I don't want to lose
mine either!

01:38.097 --> 01:41.601
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:41.668 --> 01:43.870
- I don't want to lose
my soul mate.

01:43.937 --> 01:47.807
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:47.874 --> 01:50.043
- And I don't want to lose
mine either.

01:50.109 --> 01:52.111
[laughing]

01:53.646 --> 01:56.049
- I don't want to lose
my life's work.

01:56.115 --> 02:00.019
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:00.086 --> 02:01.988
- I don't want to lose
mine either.

02:02.055 --> 02:07.227
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:07.293 --> 02:09.162
- Well, if we want
to protect our stuff,

02:09.229 --> 02:10.997
locking the door
isn't enough.

02:11.064 --> 02:13.066
We got to lock
this place down!

02:13.132 --> 02:14.067
sisters: Yeah! We do!

02:14.133 --> 02:15.602
- Ga-ga!

02:17.537 --> 02:18.671
[siren wails]

02:18.738 --> 02:20.106
- State your name
and business.

02:20.173 --> 02:21.341
{\an3}- Bobby?
What's going on?

02:21.407 --> 02:22.509
- New security measures.

02:22.575 --> 02:24.143
{\an1}Lori asked me
to protect Casa Loud.

02:24.210 --> 02:26.246
So come on, Clyde.
Name and business.

02:26.312 --> 02:28.915
- Sure. But wait,
you just said my name.

02:28.982 --> 02:30.250
{\an1}- Do we have
a problem here?

02:30.316 --> 02:31.317
- It's okay,
Boo Boo Bear.

02:31.384 --> 02:32.619
I'll vouch for him.

02:32.685 --> 02:33.887
Go ahead, Clyde.

02:33.953 --> 02:36.656
{\an3}- Thanks,
L-L-Lori.

02:36.723 --> 02:38.224
She vouched for me.

02:38.291 --> 02:41.461
[hyperventilating]

02:41.528 --> 02:44.297
[horns blare]
[alarm wailing]

02:44.364 --> 02:45.698
{\an1}- Ah!
Splendid.

02:45.765 --> 02:48.501
{\an1}My motion sensors
are working perfectly.

02:49.736 --> 02:50.670
[laser humming]

02:50.737 --> 02:52.138
- Ahh!
[thwack]

02:52.205 --> 02:53.306
- Excellent.

02:53.373 --> 02:55.441
My staircase ramp
is also working.

02:55.508 --> 02:57.744
Now to check
the alligator pit.

02:57.810 --> 02:59.913
- Noooo!
<i>[bell ringing]</i>

02:59.979 --> 03:02.248
<i>[noir music]</i>

03:02.315 --> 03:04.017
{\an1}Agent McBride
reporting for duty.

03:04.083 --> 03:05.985
{\an3}- Welcome to
the command center, McBride.

03:06.052 --> 03:07.654
{\an3}Anything goes down
in Royal Woods,

03:07.720 --> 03:09.656
we'll be the first
to know about it.

03:09.722 --> 03:12.191
- Coffee?
- You read my mind.

03:12.258 --> 03:13.793
[both slurping]

03:13.860 --> 03:14.994
[coffee splashing]

03:15.061 --> 03:16.763
I'll go get us
some juice...

03:16.829 --> 03:18.231
and some napkins.

03:18.298 --> 03:19.866
<i>[radio static crackles]</i>
<i>- Attention, all units.</i>

03:19.933 --> 03:21.367
<i>We've got an 11-25</i>
<i>at 7 Mile and Oak.</i>

03:21.434 --> 03:23.903
- An 11-25?
What's that?

03:23.970 --> 03:25.505
{\an1}- "Failure
to pick up dog poop."

03:25.572 --> 03:27.640
{\an3}- This used to be
a nice town.

03:31.044 --> 03:32.412
{\an3}- Uh,
what's going on?

03:32.478 --> 03:34.547
- Brother, if you have
valuables to protect,

03:34.614 --> 03:36.449
you can store them
in the safe room.

03:36.516 --> 03:38.685
{\an3}- Why is the bathroom
the safe room?

03:38.751 --> 03:41.554
{\an1}- Because of the cameras
I installed last year.

03:41.621 --> 03:43.756
{\an3}- You installed
cameras?

03:43.823 --> 03:45.758
- No-o-o.

03:47.694 --> 03:50.396
- I think it's the perfect place
to dump our stuff.

03:50.463 --> 03:52.999
{\an1}[laughing]
Get it?

03:53.066 --> 03:54.267
- Whoa, toots.

03:54.334 --> 03:55.802
{\an3}You're leaving me
locked in here

03:55.868 --> 03:57.070
with Count Creepy?

03:57.136 --> 03:58.371
- Ugh, please.

03:58.438 --> 04:00.974
{\an1}Edwin's the one
who should be complaining.

04:01.040 --> 04:02.675
- O...kay.

04:02.742 --> 04:04.243
- It's the burglar!

04:04.310 --> 04:05.445
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

04:05.511 --> 04:07.880
- Leni, what's
your first move?

04:07.947 --> 04:09.415
- Heyyyyy.

04:09.482 --> 04:11.918
So, like, how long
have you been burgling?

04:11.985 --> 04:13.419
- What are you doing?

04:13.486 --> 04:16.055
- Breaking the ice!
He's cute.

04:16.122 --> 04:17.490
[camera snaps]

04:17.557 --> 04:18.791
- Ugh, okay.

04:18.858 --> 04:22.161
{\an3}Lola, this burglar
just stole your tiaras.

04:22.228 --> 04:23.830
- Hi-yah!
[punches landing]

04:23.896 --> 04:26.566
- Lola! I think he liked me!

04:26.633 --> 04:28.167
- [gasps]
The burglar!

04:28.234 --> 04:29.202
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:29.268 --> 04:30.870
- Chill,
banana boy.

04:30.937 --> 04:33.840
I'm training Charles
to be a vicious guard dog.

04:33.906 --> 04:35.675
I'm the burglar!

04:35.742 --> 04:36.909
Attack, boy!

04:36.976 --> 04:38.511
- [whimpers]

04:38.578 --> 04:39.612
{\an1}[snoring]

04:39.679 --> 04:42.382
{\an3}- Look! I'm stealing
your food!

04:42.448 --> 04:43.750
- [growls lightly]

04:43.816 --> 04:45.084
- [chewing loudly]

04:45.151 --> 04:47.086
{\an3}Ugh!
Charles!

04:47.153 --> 04:49.589
{\an3}Mmm, what is this,
chipped beef?

04:54.160 --> 04:55.595
{\an1}- Got my
dancing shoes on,

04:55.662 --> 04:59.132
{\an1}and I am ready to get down
and get back up again!

04:59.198 --> 05:00.667
Rat-ta-ta!
Look-ah-oh.

05:00.733 --> 05:03.102
[siren wails]
- State your names and business.

05:03.169 --> 05:04.804
Sorry,
new security measures.

05:04.871 --> 05:07.306
- You hear that, honey?
New security measures.

05:07.373 --> 05:09.308
{\an1}I think I've really
gotten through to the kids.

05:09.375 --> 05:10.877
Thank you, Bobby!

05:10.943 --> 05:12.679
- Sorry, Mr. and Mrs. Loud,
but before you go dancing,

05:12.745 --> 05:14.781
{\an3}I really do need
your names and business.

05:14.847 --> 05:17.483
- Uh, you just said
our names and business.

05:17.550 --> 05:19.852
{\an3}- Dang it! I got to stop
doing that!

05:19.919 --> 05:22.855
{\an3}- [snoring]

05:24.524 --> 05:26.426
<i>[radio static crackles]</i>
<i>- Attention, all units.</i>

05:26.492 --> 05:28.628
<i>We've got a 10-15</i>
<i>at 8 Mile and Lindbrook.</i>

05:28.695 --> 05:30.163
<i>[bell rings]</i>
- 10-15! Oh, no!

05:30.229 --> 05:34.000
I missed my curfew.
- No, Clyde, that's a code.

05:34.067 --> 05:35.601
[gasps]

05:35.668 --> 05:37.937
You guys!
They caught the burglar!

05:38.004 --> 05:40.640
[all cheering]

05:40.707 --> 05:41.808
- Oh, Donny!

05:41.874 --> 05:43.076
We should've
run off to Mexico

05:43.142 --> 05:44.711
while we had the chance.

05:46.446 --> 05:48.514
[tires screech]

05:48.581 --> 05:50.750
{\an3}- I tell ya, honey,
one lesson in the hustle,

05:50.817 --> 05:52.218
and I am a pro.

05:52.285 --> 05:53.686
{\an3}Rat-ta-ta--
Oh!

05:53.753 --> 05:55.121
[thud]

05:55.188 --> 05:57.557
- Why don't you hustle in
and get me a towel?

05:57.623 --> 05:59.092
[keys jingle]
<i>[drumroll]</i>

05:59.158 --> 06:00.493
- Oh, come on!

06:00.560 --> 06:03.296
{\an1}- Eddie baby! Call me!
We'll do lunch!

06:03.362 --> 06:06.365
What? He's spooky, but he's
got a heart of porcelain.

06:06.432 --> 06:09.869
- Guys, I just found
the door wide open!

06:09.936 --> 06:11.938
What gives?
- Oh, we're sorry, Dad.

06:12.004 --> 06:13.706
But we don't
have to worry anymore.

06:13.773 --> 06:15.208
They caught
the burglar.

06:15.274 --> 06:16.609
- That's peachy, son,

06:16.676 --> 06:18.044
{\an3}but there could be
other burglars out there!

06:18.111 --> 06:19.479
- Actually, Father,

06:19.545 --> 06:21.314
based on Royal Woods'
crime rates per capita,

06:21.380 --> 06:23.049
that is
statistically unlikely.

06:23.116 --> 06:25.651
- Yeah, I've been listening
to the scanner all day,

06:25.718 --> 06:27.253
and the worst crime
I've heard about

06:27.320 --> 06:29.322
is someone not picking up
their dog poop.

06:29.388 --> 06:30.690
{\an1}- Where?
I'll pick it up!

06:30.757 --> 06:32.325
- But, kids--
- Oh, calm down.

06:32.391 --> 06:33.593
- Yeah, Dad.
- It'll be okay.

06:33.659 --> 06:35.528
{\an3}- Why does nobody
listen to me?

06:35.595 --> 06:39.165
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

06:39.232 --> 06:41.033
- Uh, honey?

06:41.100 --> 06:42.535
<i>- Off to dance class, kids!</i>

06:42.602 --> 06:44.704
{\an3}Please keep the door locked
while we're gone.

06:44.771 --> 06:47.006
- Sure, I got it.
- Get right on that.

06:47.073 --> 06:48.274
{\an3}- [sighs]

06:48.341 --> 06:50.743
<i>[engine turning over]</i>

06:50.810 --> 06:54.247
<i>- Help! Help!</i>
<i>I've been robbed!</i>

06:54.313 --> 06:55.381
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:55.448 --> 06:56.883
- Mr. Grouse!
What happened?

06:56.949 --> 06:59.318
{\an3}- They cleaned me out!
My polka records!

06:59.385 --> 07:01.187
My black-and-white TV!

07:01.254 --> 07:04.123
{\an3}My encyclopedias!
All gone!

07:04.190 --> 07:05.691
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:05.758 --> 07:07.760
- I literally don't know
what any of those things are.

07:07.827 --> 07:10.429
{\an1}- Dad was right.
There are other burglars.

07:10.496 --> 07:12.565
both: And our house
could be next!

07:12.632 --> 07:15.635
{\an3}- Not if we have
anything to say about it.

07:15.701 --> 07:19.572
{\an3}- Eddie, baby!
I brought my pinochle deck!

07:20.807 --> 07:22.408
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:22.475 --> 07:24.510
- You guys,
I found a deadly spray

07:24.577 --> 07:26.245
to use against
the burglar.

07:26.312 --> 07:28.848
See?
"Fatal Encounter."

07:28.915 --> 07:31.551
{\an1}- Leni, that's
a perfume sample.

07:31.617 --> 07:34.220
{\an3}- Siblings, I'm enhancing
my security system.

07:34.287 --> 07:36.222
I need a retina scan.

07:36.289 --> 07:37.657
[scanner beeping]

07:37.723 --> 07:39.358
{\an3}I also need
a stool sample.

07:39.425 --> 07:41.060
{\an1}- For your
security system?

07:41.127 --> 07:45.731
- Uh, sure, that's it.

07:45.798 --> 07:46.966
[sizzling]

07:49.535 --> 07:51.838
{\an3}- Operation Grease Release
is a go.

07:51.904 --> 07:53.606
{\an3}Let's get this baby
upstairs.

07:53.673 --> 07:55.241
{\an1}- What do we do
with all the bacon?

07:55.308 --> 07:58.444
{\an3}- That's a high-class problem
to have, my friend.

07:58.511 --> 08:00.446
- [barking]
- Charles!

08:02.682 --> 08:05.685
You're supposed to chomp
burglar butts, not bacon.

08:05.751 --> 08:08.421
[sighs]
I should've trained the cat.

08:08.487 --> 08:12.258
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:12.325 --> 08:14.460
[barbwire squeaking,
shovel scraping]

08:15.895 --> 08:18.965
- These will put a ro-dent
in the burglar's plans!

08:19.031 --> 08:20.299
[laughing]

08:20.366 --> 08:22.168
Get it?
They're mousetraps.

08:22.235 --> 08:23.236
- [groans]
- Really, dude?

08:23.302 --> 08:24.537
{\an3}- Ow!

08:24.604 --> 08:26.005
- Hey, Bobby.

08:26.072 --> 08:28.641
- My Roller Derby team
is gonna help you patrol.

08:28.708 --> 08:32.178
{\an3}- Hmm. Do they have
any policing experience?

08:32.245 --> 08:34.145
- No, but they can do this.

08:35.280 --> 08:36.916
[thud]
- [groans]

08:36.982 --> 08:38.551
You're hired.

08:38.618 --> 08:39.751
[alarm blares]

08:40.620 --> 08:41.953
[metal screeches]

08:43.856 --> 08:45.224
- Good evening,
parental units.

08:45.291 --> 08:48.227
{\an1}We are going to need to conduct
a routine body search.

08:48.294 --> 08:50.963
{\an3}- What in the world
is going on?

08:51.030 --> 08:54.300
{\an1}- Mr. Grouse got robbed.
We had to beef up security.

08:54.367 --> 08:55.801
- We used
your credit card.

08:55.868 --> 08:57.503
- Kids, I'm glad you're
taking this seriously,

08:57.570 --> 08:59.238
but you may have gone
a little overboard.

08:59.305 --> 09:00.539
{\an3}- A little?

09:00.606 --> 09:02.241
{\an3}- We don't need
all this security.

09:02.308 --> 09:04.343
{\an3}If we just lock the doors
and windows, we'll be fine.

09:04.410 --> 09:05.678
Now, everyone to bed.

09:05.745 --> 09:06.979
- Okay, Dad.
- If you say so.

09:07.046 --> 09:09.482
{\an1}- I'm still gonna need
those stool samples.

09:09.548 --> 09:12.485
<i>[sneaky music]</i>

09:12.551 --> 09:19.492
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:19.558 --> 09:21.060
[knocking]

09:21.127 --> 09:22.628
{\an3}- Thanks for pretending
to be robbed.

09:22.695 --> 09:24.563
{\an3}I think my kids
really learned their lesson.

09:24.630 --> 09:25.898
{\an1}- I would have scared them
for free,

09:25.965 --> 09:28.935
{\an1}but I'll gladly
take your muffins.

09:29.001 --> 09:34.340
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:34.407 --> 09:37.310
- Lock.
Dad would be so proud.

09:37.376 --> 09:38.344
[doorknob rattling]

09:38.411 --> 09:40.279
- [groans]

09:40.346 --> 09:43.182
[crickets chirping]

09:43.249 --> 09:44.283
[grunting]

09:44.350 --> 09:45.284
[yells]

09:45.351 --> 09:46.285
[thud]

09:46.352 --> 09:47.586
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:47.653 --> 09:49.121
- [gasps]

09:49.188 --> 09:52.124
[bells ringing]

09:52.191 --> 09:53.326
Battle stations, guys!

09:53.392 --> 09:55.328
{\an3}We've got a burglar
on the premises!

09:55.394 --> 09:56.462
[all gasp]

09:56.529 --> 09:57.763
- Oh, my gosh,
what do we do?

09:57.830 --> 09:59.365
{\an3}He's gonna
take all our stuff!

09:59.432 --> 10:01.233
{\an1}- Get it together,
woman!

10:01.300 --> 10:03.135
{\an3}- Thanks,
I needed that.

10:03.202 --> 10:04.971
But I'll get you back.

10:05.037 --> 10:06.272
- [whimpers]

10:06.339 --> 10:09.075
{\an1}- Don't trouble yourself
or anything, Charles.

10:09.141 --> 10:10.076
- [whines]

10:10.142 --> 10:11.744
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:11.811 --> 10:13.179
[air horn blares]
- Ow, ow, ow!

10:13.245 --> 10:14.347
Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow!

10:14.413 --> 10:16.515
{\an1}- Eat hot
bacon grease!

10:16.582 --> 10:20.619
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:20.686 --> 10:23.589
{\an1}Make that
congealed bacon grease.

10:23.656 --> 10:25.691
[bell rings]

10:25.758 --> 10:27.727
[siren wails]
Keep a tight formation, ladies.

10:27.793 --> 10:29.528
This is what
we trained for!

10:29.595 --> 10:30.963
[punches landing]

10:31.030 --> 10:33.566
- Wait, wait!
I recognize those dancing shoes.

10:33.632 --> 10:34.834
Off! Off!

10:36.736 --> 10:37.803
all: Dad!

10:37.870 --> 10:39.739
- I...was just
taking a walk

10:39.805 --> 10:41.173
and I got locked out.

10:41.240 --> 10:42.742
- We're so sorry!
- Sorry, Dad.

10:42.808 --> 10:44.076
- We're so sorry.
- Hey, Loud!

10:44.143 --> 10:46.579
These muffins
got walnuts in them.

10:46.645 --> 10:50.016
Next time you want to pay me off
for pretending to be robbed,

10:50.082 --> 10:53.686
how about giving me something
I'm not allergic to?

10:53.753 --> 10:55.588
- Pretending to be robbed?

10:55.654 --> 10:56.856
- Dad!
- Our own father.

10:56.922 --> 10:58.858
- You lied to us?
- Bogus move, Dad.

10:58.924 --> 11:00.793
- [sighs]
I'm sorry, everyone.

11:00.860 --> 11:03.195
I was just trying to teach you
to lock the dang door.

11:03.262 --> 11:06.098
I just want to protect
my most important valuables...

11:06.165 --> 11:07.099
you guys.

11:07.166 --> 11:08.334
all: Aww!

11:08.401 --> 11:09.735
- Okay, Dad,
we'll lock the door.

11:09.802 --> 11:11.604
- You're the greatest.
- Love you.

11:11.670 --> 11:12.838
- [whimpers]

11:14.173 --> 11:15.107
[barks]

11:15.174 --> 11:16.275
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:16.342 --> 11:17.276
[crunch]
- Ouch!

11:17.343 --> 11:18.277
- Finally!

11:22.348 --> 11:25.284
<i>[rock music]</i>

11:25.351 --> 11:31.290
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:31.357 --> 11:33.893
[birds chirping]

11:33.959 --> 11:36.695
- Hold still.

11:36.762 --> 11:37.897
{\an1}Got it!

11:37.963 --> 11:39.498
{\an3}- Whoa!
Great shot!

11:39.565 --> 11:41.200
First mustache hair ever.

11:41.267 --> 11:44.203
{\an3}This one's definitely going
in the "Lincoln Library."

11:44.270 --> 11:46.038
- Lincoln library?

11:46.105 --> 11:47.440
<i>[jazzy music]</i>

11:47.506 --> 11:48.674
{\an3}- Yep,
it's the folder

11:48.741 --> 11:50.409
{\an3}where I keep all
my cherished memories.

11:50.476 --> 11:51.677
Check it out.

11:51.744 --> 11:53.179
Here's me and Lynn
in the bathtub.

11:53.245 --> 11:55.181
Lori feeding me
my first ice cream.

11:55.247 --> 11:56.749
My first
mechanical pony ride.

11:56.816 --> 11:59.718
And now
my first mustache hair--

12:05.057 --> 12:06.492
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

12:06.559 --> 12:08.360
Whoa!
Where you going?

12:08.427 --> 12:10.096
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:10.162 --> 12:11.263
[gasps]
No, no, no, no, no!

12:11.330 --> 12:12.364
Sto-o-op!

12:12.431 --> 12:14.567
Oh, no, no, no, no, no!

12:16.168 --> 12:17.803
[gasps]
All my childhood memories

12:17.870 --> 12:19.038
are gone!

12:19.105 --> 12:20.072
- Don't worry, buddy.

12:20.139 --> 12:21.173
This happened to me once,

12:21.240 --> 12:22.508
but I got them all back.

12:22.575 --> 12:24.210
{\an1}My dads saved them
in the cloud.

12:24.276 --> 12:25.277
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:25.344 --> 12:26.445
- What do you think,
Charles?

12:26.512 --> 12:28.614
More cheese,
less cheese?

12:28.681 --> 12:30.483
- [barks]
- You're right.

12:30.549 --> 12:32.251
Always more cheese.
- Dad!

12:32.318 --> 12:33.352
Do we have
the cloud?

12:33.419 --> 12:34.854
{\an1}- Well, of course
we do, Lincoln.

12:34.920 --> 12:36.122
{\an1}- [sighs]

12:36.188 --> 12:39.125
{\an1}- We also have the sky
and the sun and the moon--

12:39.191 --> 12:40.926
{\an1}- No, I mean
the digital cloud,

12:40.993 --> 12:43.162
{\an1}where you store stuff
from your computer.

12:43.229 --> 12:45.264
- Oh, that cloud!

12:45.331 --> 12:46.265
{\an1}No.

12:46.332 --> 12:47.633
- [whimpers]

12:49.001 --> 12:51.303
{\an1}I can't believe it--
all my childhood memories

12:51.370 --> 12:52.838
gone forever.

12:52.905 --> 12:54.140
- Let it out, buddy.

12:54.206 --> 12:56.142
{\an3}Dr. Lopez says,
"The first step of healing

12:56.208 --> 12:57.576
{\an3}is to honor
your feelings."

12:57.643 --> 13:00.045
- No, no, no, no, no!
Charles, bad!

13:00.112 --> 13:01.213
I hate Mondays.

13:01.280 --> 13:02.448
[sighs]

13:02.515 --> 13:04.183
Guess I'll just
have to remake it.

13:04.250 --> 13:05.684
- Remake it?

13:05.751 --> 13:07.186
Clyde, that's the answer!

13:07.253 --> 13:08.320
- Good idea.

13:08.387 --> 13:09.688
Helping your dad
with his lasagna

13:09.755 --> 13:11.390
{\an3}might take your mind
off your loss.

13:11.457 --> 13:12.958
That's the second
step of healing.

13:13.025 --> 13:15.594
{\an1}- No, I mean
we'll remake the photos.

13:15.661 --> 13:16.996
{\an3}- Hmm.
Denial.

13:17.062 --> 13:19.064
That's actually
a step backwards.

13:19.131 --> 13:20.566
But I'm in!

13:20.633 --> 13:23.202
- Guys,
hallway meeting!

13:23.269 --> 13:24.703
{\an1}- Ho, ho,
this better be good.

13:24.770 --> 13:26.572
{\an1}I was in the middle
of my lunges.

13:26.639 --> 13:27.840
- Oh, it's better
than good.

13:27.907 --> 13:29.575
Who wants to have
a really fun day

13:29.642 --> 13:32.344
re-creating some classic
family photos?

13:32.411 --> 13:34.680
- Uh, hard pass.

13:34.747 --> 13:36.448
{\an1}- Sorry, dude. We're all
headed to the mall.

13:36.515 --> 13:38.384
{\an1}Big sale
on studded chokers.

13:38.450 --> 13:40.152
- And coffin linings.

13:40.219 --> 13:42.354
- And dual-flush toilets.

13:43.856 --> 13:46.859
{\an3}- Dang it.
We need a plan B.

13:46.926 --> 13:49.028
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:49.094 --> 13:50.663
- Or do we need a...

13:50.729 --> 13:52.364
{\an1}plan C?

13:52.431 --> 13:54.400
{\an1}Get it?
The C is for Clyde.

13:54.466 --> 13:55.968
{\an3}- I get it,
and I like it.

13:56.035 --> 13:59.038
But wait, do you really think
you can play all my sisters?

13:59.104 --> 14:00.906
- Pssh, my dads and I
have been doing

14:00.973 --> 14:03.142
Friday night scene study
for years.

14:03.209 --> 14:05.578
I once played
all the orphans in "Annie."

14:05.644 --> 14:08.113
Ever heard of it?
Now get me my plunger!

14:08.180 --> 14:12.017
- Wow, you have more layers
than my dad's lasagna.

14:12.084 --> 14:15.588
Okay, first shot--
me and Lynn in the tub.

14:15.654 --> 14:18.224
And this time, we're not
taking any chances.

14:18.290 --> 14:20.593
I'm gonna use film
and print hard copies.

14:20.659 --> 14:23.028
{\an3}- Whatever, nerd.
Who uses film anymore?

14:23.095 --> 14:25.030
Think fast!
- Oof!

14:25.097 --> 14:26.565
Clyde, what gives?

14:26.632 --> 14:28.734
{\an3}- Sorry, Lincoln.
Just getting into character.

14:28.801 --> 14:30.736
It's an actor thing.

14:30.803 --> 14:33.472
- Okay,
light's good.

14:33.539 --> 14:35.474
Water's good.

14:35.541 --> 14:36.775
Props are ready.

14:36.842 --> 14:38.877
[camera timer whirring]
Timer's set.

14:38.944 --> 14:40.312
[water splashes]

14:40.379 --> 14:41.413
[water bubbles]

14:41.480 --> 14:42.715
- Submarine destroyer!

14:42.781 --> 14:44.550
- Aw, man!
You farted?

14:44.617 --> 14:46.252
{\an3}- It felt right,
and I went with it.

14:46.318 --> 14:48.287
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

14:48.354 --> 14:49.722
[pbbbt]
[camera shutter snaps]

14:49.788 --> 14:52.758
- Next up: Lori feeding me
my first ice cream.

14:52.825 --> 14:55.294
Chair is at optimal height.

14:55.361 --> 14:56.795
Ice cream
is mint chocolate chip.

14:56.862 --> 14:59.765
Diaper is snug
but not restrictive.

14:59.832 --> 15:03.135
Clyde,
I'm ready for you on set!

15:03.202 --> 15:04.303
Clyde?

15:04.370 --> 15:06.238
Pfft.
Actors.

15:06.305 --> 15:09.475
Ahhhgh!
[thud]

15:09.541 --> 15:11.777
{\an1}- Sorry,
I was just, uh...

15:11.844 --> 15:13.612
{\an1}doing some
character work.

15:13.679 --> 15:15.447
<i>[rock music]</i>

15:15.514 --> 15:16.849
[smooching]

15:16.915 --> 15:19.218
Sorry, Bobby.
It's literally over.

15:19.285 --> 15:20.986
I'm in love with Clyde.

15:21.053 --> 15:22.655
[camera timer whirring]

15:22.721 --> 15:25.791
{\an3}Well, it worked,
'cause you look just like Lori.

15:25.858 --> 15:27.293
{\an1}- Really?

15:27.359 --> 15:29.261
L-L-L-Lori?

15:29.328 --> 15:30.262
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

15:30.329 --> 15:31.597
{\an1}[groans]

15:31.664 --> 15:34.199
- Next up: my first
mechanical pony ride

15:34.266 --> 15:35.768
with Lucy and Luan.

15:35.834 --> 15:37.469
- I could have
played both roles.

15:37.536 --> 15:39.138
You didn't have
to hire an amateur.

15:39.204 --> 15:40.639
- Wassup, playas?

15:40.706 --> 15:42.741
{\an3}Lucy Loud
is in the house!

15:42.808 --> 15:44.343
{\an1}- Rusty,
a little acting tip.

15:44.410 --> 15:45.878
{\an1}Lucy would never
say that.

15:45.944 --> 15:47.813
- You just worry
about your Lola.

15:47.880 --> 15:50.883
- I'm Luan! Did you
at all prepare for this?

15:50.949 --> 15:53.085
{\an1}- Guys, let's just
get the shot.

15:53.152 --> 15:55.054
[camera timer whirring]

15:55.120 --> 15:57.323
<i>[mechanical pony</i>
<i>music playing]</i>

15:57.389 --> 15:59.258
[all scream]

15:59.325 --> 16:00.993
[camera shutter snaps]

16:01.060 --> 16:03.862
{\an3}- Wow, that's really putting
the cart before the horse!

16:03.929 --> 16:05.864
{\an3}[laughing]
Get it?

16:05.931 --> 16:06.732
[knocking]

16:06.799 --> 16:08.200
- What is it, Loud?

16:08.267 --> 16:09.201
- Hey, Mr. Grouse.

16:09.268 --> 16:10.402
We're taking a photo

16:10.469 --> 16:14.073
{\an1}and we really need
someone to play Santa.

16:14.139 --> 16:16.742
- Hard pass.

16:16.809 --> 16:20.012
- What if I can make it
worth your while?

16:20.079 --> 16:21.480
- [munching]

16:21.547 --> 16:23.048
I'm not a fan
of playing dress-up,

16:23.115 --> 16:25.050
but I do love
your dad's lasagna.

16:25.117 --> 16:28.787
{\an3}- Okay, I did not think
you'd eat the whole tray,

16:28.854 --> 16:31.056
{\an3}but I'm sure we can find
something else for dinner.

16:31.123 --> 16:32.591
{\an3}We're burning daylight,
people.

16:32.658 --> 16:35.060
Where's my elf?
- One sec, Lincoln.

16:35.127 --> 16:36.562
Just have to finish
this train.

16:36.628 --> 16:38.697
[crunch]
Ow!

16:38.764 --> 16:40.399
{\an3}- Clyde,
you stand here.

16:40.466 --> 16:41.567
- [snoring]

16:41.633 --> 16:43.068
[camera timer whirring]

16:43.135 --> 16:44.069
{\an1}Oof!

16:44.136 --> 16:45.070
{\an1}[belches]

16:45.137 --> 16:47.172
[thud]
- Ow!

16:47.239 --> 16:48.240
{\an3}[yelps]

16:48.307 --> 16:49.241
[camera shutter snaps]

16:50.409 --> 16:52.111
- Okay, Clyde,
moment of truth.

16:52.177 --> 16:54.380
Let's see how
our first roll came out.

16:54.446 --> 16:57.383
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

16:57.449 --> 16:59.251
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:59.318 --> 17:01.253
both: These...are...

17:01.320 --> 17:02.821
awesome!

17:02.888 --> 17:05.223
- I'm not gonna lose my
childhood memories after all!

17:05.290 --> 17:06.392
{\an3}- Whoo-hoo!

17:06.458 --> 17:07.859
{\an3}So what's
our next scene?

17:07.925 --> 17:09.560
- It's my seventh birthday.

17:09.627 --> 17:11.329
{\an3}- Great!
Will it require an accent?

17:11.396 --> 17:12.731
Do I need to gain weight?

17:12.798 --> 17:14.833
{\an1}- Thank you Clyde,
but that won't be necessary.

17:14.900 --> 17:17.102
- I also do my own stunts.

17:17.169 --> 17:18.503
{\an1}[yells]

17:18.569 --> 17:20.038
[clang]

17:20.105 --> 17:21.640
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

17:21.707 --> 17:23.108
[both panting]

17:23.175 --> 17:25.010
{\an1}- So glad we still
have this thing.

17:25.077 --> 17:28.213
{\an3}- Wish you still had
the pump, though.

17:28.280 --> 17:29.882
{\an3}[gasps]

17:29.948 --> 17:31.517
- Wait...
my seventh birthday

17:31.583 --> 17:33.719
didn't have
a bounce house.

17:33.786 --> 17:35.687
It was
a lucha libre party.

17:35.754 --> 17:37.623
- [whimpers]

17:37.689 --> 17:40.058
{\an1}- Come on, Clyde.
We need to redress the set.

17:40.125 --> 17:42.127
{\an3}- I think I need to go
lie down for a minute...

17:42.194 --> 17:43.896
in Lori's bed.

17:44.963 --> 17:46.832
- If I remember
the photo right,

17:46.899 --> 17:49.835
I was on the ground and Lynn
was leaping on top of me.

17:49.902 --> 17:51.437
{\an1}- Cool,
just give me a second

17:51.503 --> 17:53.005
to get back into
Lynn's character.

17:53.071 --> 17:55.607
{\an1}[grunts]
Okay, good to go!

17:55.674 --> 17:57.042
[camera timer whirring]

17:57.109 --> 17:58.477
<i>[Mexican hat dance playing]</i>

17:58.544 --> 18:00.646
{\an1}Lunatic Lynn
off the third turnbuckle!

18:00.712 --> 18:02.381
{\an1}Aieeeeeee!

18:02.448 --> 18:03.449
- [gasps]
Wait a minute!

18:03.515 --> 18:04.516
[thud]
- Oof!

18:04.583 --> 18:06.218
- It wasn't
lucha libre.

18:06.285 --> 18:07.920
It was circus-themed!

18:07.986 --> 18:10.055
{\an1}- I'll get
my clown shoes.

18:10.122 --> 18:12.391
<i>[playful music]</i>

18:12.458 --> 18:13.826
{\an1}- Wait,
it wasn't a clown.

18:13.892 --> 18:16.195
It was a lion tamer.
- [yells]

18:16.261 --> 18:17.196
[thud]
Ooh!

18:17.262 --> 18:18.964
- Out of my...
[belches]

18:19.031 --> 18:20.032
Yard!

18:20.098 --> 18:21.834
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:21.900 --> 18:23.735
- Wait,
it wasn't a lion tamer.

18:23.802 --> 18:25.304
It was a contortionist.

18:25.370 --> 18:27.072
[cat snarling]

18:27.139 --> 18:29.308
No, it wasn't
a contortionist.

18:29.374 --> 18:32.377
It was a guy
shot out of a cannon.

18:32.444 --> 18:33.378
[thud]

18:33.445 --> 18:34.513
<i>[marching band music]</i>

18:34.580 --> 18:36.181
Hmm,
wait a minute.

18:36.248 --> 18:37.916
{\an3}- Oh, no, are you
changing your mind?

18:37.983 --> 18:39.218
{\an3}'Cause if you're
changing your mind,

18:39.284 --> 18:41.119
{\an3}you should definitely
get me out of

18:41.186 --> 18:42.621
heeeeeeeere!

18:42.688 --> 18:44.790
{\an1}- What did we do
at that party?

18:44.857 --> 18:46.391
{\an3}Sorry to put you
through that, buddy.

18:46.458 --> 18:47.826
- That's okay, Lincoln.

18:47.893 --> 18:49.561
It was nothing compared
to the roof tumble I took

18:49.628 --> 18:51.663
during "Fiddler" last
Friday Family Theater night.

18:51.730 --> 18:53.031
- We got a problem, Clyde.

18:53.098 --> 18:55.200
{\an3}My memories are starting
to slip away.

18:55.267 --> 18:57.870
{\an3}We need to get through
the rest of these photos fast.

18:57.936 --> 19:00.606
{\an1}- No problem.
Just let me get some new pants.

19:00.672 --> 19:01.740
<i>[fast-paced string music]</i>

19:01.807 --> 19:02.774
[camera timer whirring]

19:02.841 --> 19:04.276
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:04.343 --> 19:06.011
[camera shutter snaps]

19:06.078 --> 19:06.845
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:06.912 --> 19:08.647
[camera shutter snaps]

19:08.714 --> 19:09.681
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:09.748 --> 19:11.049
[camera shutter snaps]

19:11.116 --> 19:11.884
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:11.950 --> 19:13.385
[camera shutter snaps]

19:13.452 --> 19:14.386
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:14.453 --> 19:16.088
[camera shutter snaps]

19:16.154 --> 19:16.922
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:16.989 --> 19:18.557
[camera shutter snaps]

19:18.624 --> 19:19.591
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:19.658 --> 19:21.193
[camera shutter snaps]

19:21.260 --> 19:22.027
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:22.094 --> 19:23.729
[camera shutter snaps]

19:23.795 --> 19:24.863
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:24.930 --> 19:26.465
[camera shutter snaps]

19:26.532 --> 19:27.466
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:27.533 --> 19:30.002
[camera shutter snapping]

19:30.068 --> 19:31.537
[both breathing heavily]

19:31.603 --> 19:33.038
sisters: Lincoln!

19:33.105 --> 19:34.907
- What are you doing
with all our stuff?

19:34.973 --> 19:37.009
- [gasps] That tiara is never

19:37.075 --> 19:39.511
supposed to touch the ground!

19:39.578 --> 19:40.913
- Ladies, don't worry.

19:40.979 --> 19:42.581
I'm going
to put everything back

19:42.648 --> 19:44.249
right after
I develop this--

19:44.316 --> 19:45.250
[fly buzzing]

19:45.317 --> 19:46.585
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

19:46.652 --> 19:48.820
Nooooooooo!

19:48.887 --> 19:51.523
I can't believe
I forgot to load the film.

19:51.590 --> 19:53.392
[groans]
[thud]

19:53.458 --> 19:55.327
Potty, sandbox,

19:55.394 --> 19:56.962
lion tamer, lasagna...

19:57.029 --> 19:58.931
{\an1}- Lincoln!
Snap out of it!

19:58.997 --> 20:00.799
You're babbling!

20:00.866 --> 20:02.034
- Are you okay?

20:02.100 --> 20:04.136
{\an1}Clyde told us
what you were trying to do.

20:04.202 --> 20:05.771
{\an1}- Then he caught a glimpse
of Lori

20:05.837 --> 20:07.306
and lost consciousness.

20:07.372 --> 20:10.309
- L-L-L-L--
- Don't say her name so loud.

20:10.375 --> 20:12.844
- We're really sorry
you lost all your photos.

20:12.911 --> 20:14.613
Do you want us
to help you re-create them?

20:14.680 --> 20:17.683
- Yeah, I shutter to think
what you're going through.

20:17.749 --> 20:19.651
[laughing]
Get it?

20:19.718 --> 20:21.587
- [sighs]
Thanks anyway, guys,

20:21.653 --> 20:22.955
but it's useless.

20:23.021 --> 20:25.290
My childhood memories
are already gone.

20:25.357 --> 20:26.925
I can't even remember
what happened

20:26.992 --> 20:28.927
at my seventh birthday party.

20:28.994 --> 20:31.063
{\an1}- I can.
You had a magician.

20:31.129 --> 20:33.265
<i>You literally freaked out</i>
<i>about his rabbit.</i>

20:33.332 --> 20:34.700
- [screaming]

20:34.766 --> 20:35.701
- [barking]

20:35.767 --> 20:36.702
[splat]
- Oof!

20:36.768 --> 20:38.870
[laughter]

20:38.937 --> 20:40.739
- I can't believe
you remember that.

20:40.806 --> 20:42.441
- Dudes, remember
what happened

20:42.507 --> 20:44.743
at Lincoln's sixth
birthday party?

20:44.810 --> 20:47.079
{\an3}- [laughs]
At the bowling alley?

20:47.145 --> 20:48.947
I'll never forget that.

20:49.014 --> 20:52.718
- [screaming]
Oof!

20:52.784 --> 20:54.553
[laughter]

20:54.620 --> 20:57.689
{\an3}- That was the only strike
you ever got, lame-o!

20:57.756 --> 20:59.124
{\an3}- Do you guys
remember that time

20:59.191 --> 21:01.059
{\an3}when Lincoln deleted
all of his photos

21:01.126 --> 21:02.594
off the computer?

21:02.661 --> 21:04.129
{\an3}[laughing]

21:04.196 --> 21:05.831
- Uh, that was
this morning.

21:05.897 --> 21:08.033
{\an1}- [laughs]
I know! Remember?

21:08.100 --> 21:09.401
{\an3}- Yeah,
what about the time

21:09.468 --> 21:11.303
{\an3}Lincoln got
into Mom's cosmetics?

21:11.370 --> 21:13.705
<i>[playful music]</i>
- [babbles]

21:13.772 --> 21:16.208
- Now, there's a story
you couldn't makeup.

21:16.274 --> 21:17.909
[siblings groan]
